B.UB=new A.a0("Modal Verbs & Conditional Structures","Gaps in grammar directly affect clearance readbacks and PIREP accuracy. Focus on shall/must/should and if-clauses in operational contexts.")
B.UK=new A.a0("Tense Consistency in Instructions","Inconsistent tense usage causes ambiguity in traffic information. Practice passive voice and future tense in ATC coordination phrases.")
B.UV=new A.a0("Imperative & Modal Structures","Safety announcements require precise imperative and modal grammar. Passengers must receive unambiguous instructions in emergency situations.")
B.V9=new A.a0("Core Aviation Grammar Patterns","Master modal verbs, passive constructions, and conditional sentences \u2014 the three pillars of ICAO standard aviation English grammar.")
B.R3=new A.bF(B.mo,[B.UB,B.UK,B.UV,B.V9],t.dM)
B.V6=new A.a0("METAR/TAF & NOTAMs Terminology","Weather and NOTAM vocabulary is critical for pre-flight planning and in-flight decision making. Build your decoding speed for METAR abbreviations.")
B.Vb=new A.a0("SID/STAR & Holding Phraseology","Precise vocabulary for departure and arrival procedures prevents misunderstandings in high-traffic environments. Focus on ICAO Doc 4444 phraseology.")
B.V7=new A.a0("Safety Equipment Terminology","Accurate names for safety equipment and procedures are non-negotiable for ICAO compliance and passenger safety management.")
B.UG=new A.a0("ICAO Core Aviation Vocabulary","Build your foundation with ATC phraseology, aircraft systems vocabulary, and standard ICAO terminology used across all aviation roles.")
B.R4=new A.bF(B.mo,[B.V6,B.Vb,B.V7,B.UG],t.dM)
B.US=new A.a0("Operational Document Comprehension","Slow reading of NOTAMs and OFPs under time pressure is a common exam failure point. Practice extracting key data from dense aviation texts in under 90 seconds.")
B.UR=new A.a0("Flight Plan & Strip Reading Speed","ATC strips and flight plan formats contain dense information that must be processed rapidly. Drill reading speed on ICAO flight plan formats.")
B.Vk=new A.a0("Safety Procedure Manuals","Understanding company ops manuals and ICAO safety documents in English is required for all cabin crew roles. Focus on procedural language patterns.")
B.UC=new A.a0("Aviation Text Comprehension","ICAO English exams include dense operational texts. Practice reading NOTAMs, METARs, and AIP extracts \u2014 focus on identifying key information quickly.")
B.R2=new A.bF(B.mo,[B.US,B.UR,B.Vk,B.UC],t.dM)
B.mp={pilot:0,atc:1,student:2,cabin_crew:3}
B.UO=new A.a0("Operational Meaning Interpretation","Accurately interpreting the intent of ATC instructions and translating concepts between English and your working language prevents dangerous misunderstandings.")
B.UF=new A.a0("Readback & Clearance Precision","Translation errors in clearance readbacks are a leading cause of runway incursions. Practice precision in both directions without paraphrasing critical values.")
B.Vf=new A.a0("Context-Based Language Transfer","Focus on understanding aviation texts in context rather than word-for-word translation. ICAO language is formulaic \u2014 learn the patterns.")
B.UM=new A.a0("Safety Communication Accuracy","Translating safety instructions accurately ensures passenger compliance. Focus on official ICAO safety terminology rather than free translation.")
B.Ro=new A.bF(B.mp,[B.UO,B.UF,B.Vf,B.UM],t.dM)
B.UA=new A.a0("Aviation Collocations & Fixed Phrases",'Many ATC communications use fixed collocations (e.g. "cleared for", "report passing"). Recognition of these patterns is tested directly in fill-in-the-blank questions.')
B.UD=new A.a0("Standard Phraseology Patterns","Fill-in-the-blank questions test your knowledge of ICAO Doc 4444 standard phrases. Memorize the exact wording of common clearances and instructions.")
B.Vg=new A.a0("Aviation Collocation Patterns","Aviation English uses specific word combinations that don't follow general English rules. Study collocations from ICAO training materials systematically.")
B.V1=new A.a0("Safety Announcement Templates","Standard safety announcements follow fixed templates. Master the exact phrasing for each type of announcement \u2014 these appear frequently in fill-blank exams.")
B.Rm=new A.bF(B.mp,[B.UA,B.UD,B.Vg,B.V1],t.dM)
B.UE=new A.a0("Discourse Flow in ATC Communication","Understanding how ATC/pilot exchanges are structured helps predict how sentences complete. Study the logical flow of standard communication sequences.")
B.V5=new A.a0("Logical Sequence in Clearances","Clearance sentences follow predictable logical patterns. Practice completing partial clearances to build speed and accuracy on this question type.")
B.UL=new A.a0("Aviation Sentence Structure","Aviation English sentences follow specific structural patterns. Study how information is sequenced in ICAO communications \u2014 what comes first, second, third.")
B.Vd=new A.a0("Procedural Language Completion","Safety and service procedure sentences follow predictable structures. Practice with official cabin crew communication scripts to internalize the patterns.")
